document_data.name: Henrietta Storm
document_data.mainbody: '''Henrietta Storm''' was a [[tiefling]] cobbler who lived and worked in the village of [[Wisteria Vale]]. They ran the shop [[Silks and Soles]] with their business partner [[Josephus Lovett]].
document_data.Personality: Henrietta was an outgoing individual who loved gathering folks together for events in Wisteria Vale. They were especially fond of crafting decorations from spare fabric and other materials.
document_data.History: Some time during or around the {{YearlinkName|1489}}, Henrietta's likeness was recreated as an animated, wooden mannequin known as a [[constructed commoner]], which was then placed within the [[Wisteria Vale (demiplane)|demiplane]] that housed the famous [[Harper]] [[Arrant Quill]].
